The total cost of processing the visa will be lower, no longer to be payable for the meeting to be agreed, the second for the processing of the application and others for the delivery of the document by the transport service.
The applicant will only pay a single fee to cover all three services.
The current tariff will remain unchanged: an amount equivalent to $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for cases of visas with applications (including visas for temporary workers) and $390 for a visa for traders and investors.
People who want to renew their visa will not have to interview the consulator with the consulator, but will only contact the nearest ASC, where they will present their documents and take their fingerprints.
As the biometric information will be taken to ASC, applicants who will require a second meeting with an interview at the Consulatory Unit will spend a shorter time here than in the past.
